On Fri, 12 Feb 1999 sinbuxs@typeb.sita.int wrote:
> Do any one know how to configure framebuffer with S3 Verge
> video card, I have compiled the kernel (2.2.1) with framebuffer
> and vesa enabled. I do have manually created /dev/fb as mentioned
> in frambuffer kernel document.
I believe the problem is that the S3 Virge is VESA 1.2 compliant, but not
VESA 2.0 compliant. (Although I'm probably wrong. If I am wrong, then I'm
interested in the real reason, as I have an S3 Virge as well)
